Linking related issues:
[RFE: Native Mac/Windows support #8452](https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/8452) : this is closed, even though seemingly it could rely on Fedora [Platform Request - Apple native hypervisor #1533](https://github.com/coreos/fedora-coreos-tracker/issues/1533) and Fedora [Add Platform: Native Apple Hypervisor #1548](https://github.com/coreos/fedora-coreos-tracker/issues/1548), which are in progress?

@baude the article https://www.redhat.com/sysadmin/podman-mac-machine-architecture states that Podman is built on "[QEMU plus HVF](https://wiki.qemu.org/Features/HVF) acceleration: Runs a virtualized Linux distribution using native macOS virtualization", but that seems to still be in progress with [Platform Request - Apple native hypervisor #1533](https://github.com/coreos/fedora-coreos-tracker/issues/1533) , and 13 out of 44 tasks done in [Add Platform: Native Apple Hypervisor #1548](https://github.com/coreos/fedora-coreos-tracker/issues/1548) ?
